<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="81133b9c-e569-549c-bc21-e022cfbf966c" activityNameId="cc18fdd2-69d4-461a-b90d-5af9a392e7a4" parentActivityId="09fa3205-4b6f-5d2b-89a0-5dd1cb696116" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of redmud from bauxite digestion, residual material landfill</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to the water (short-term emissions to water from leachate and long-term emissions to ground water).</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'redmud from bauxite digestion' in a residual material landfill (RMLF). Recommended use of this dataset: The waste is an inorganic tailings slurry called redmud produced during the purification (digestion) of raw bauxite ore.  Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% redmud from bauxite digestion; .  Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): H2O na; O 379730; H na; C 7606.7; S 800; N na; P 1475; B 10; Cl na; Br na; F 1130; I na; Ag na; As 29; Ba na; Cd 4.5; Co 22; Cr 750.97; Cu 36.742; Hg 0.025; Mn 363.32; Mo na; Ni 5.4; Pb 14.142; Sb 0.3; Se 5; Sn na; V 535.08; Zn 36.661; Be 0.7; Sc na; Sr na; Ti 40203; Tl na; W na; Si 104470; Fe 296420; Ca 22446; Al 84217; K na; Mg na; Na 59688.  Share of carbon in initial waste input that is biogenic 0%. </text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="5e736d13-58c6-4fbd-8157-dd6ef35c3f88">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3822:Treatment and disposal of hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0c40fa1e-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">CN</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents a landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 14.2174 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 910.891 mm/year, mean annual actual evaporation (EAT) of 593.541369298096 mm/year, and net infiltration of 317.3 mm/year. The leachate percolating through the residual material landfill has an average residence time of 11 years.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">World Meteorological Organization, 2022. China Meteorological Administration and World Meteorological Organization, World Meteorological Organization Available at: https://worldweather.wmo.int/en/country.html?countryCode=1</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Residual material landfill for polluted, inorganic waste (VVEA Type C). With base seal and leachate collection system. Ultimate average landfill height is 10 meters. Operation phase duration is 30 years. Recultivation after closure. No additional solidification with cement requested. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase in the residual material landfill is estimated to be reached after 60 000 years.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
